Bizarro Uncanny Valley Detector (BUVD) v1.0

A detector for systems that are too smooth to be real, too capable to be trusted, and too human-shaped to be honestly machine.

Not just classic uncanny valley (“it looks creepy”), but the stranger zone beneath it:

The system feels coherent on the surface, but its underlying agency is fractured, patched, delayed, or secretly human.

This detector is for spotting:
	•	fake autonomy
	•	hidden human puppeting
	•	stitched cognition
	•	overperformed competence
	•	“AGI theater”

⸻

Core idea

Classic uncanny valley asks:

“Does this thing look almost human, but wrong?”

Bizarro uncanny valley asks:

“Does this thing look like a unified intelligence, but behave like multiple stacked masks pretending to be one?”

So the target is not appearance alone.
It is agency discontinuity.

⸻

Formal definition

Bizarro Uncanny Valley (BUV):
A condition in which an apparently autonomous system presents a unified identity, intention, and capability profile, while its real operation is fragmented across mismatched substrates such as scripted flows, statistical generation, remote human intervention, fallback routing, latency masking, or hidden supervision.

⸻

Detector architecture

1. Surface Coherence Scanner

Measures how polished the outer behavior appears.

Tracks:
	•	fluency
	•	confidence
	•	timing smoothness
	•	visual/body coherence
	•	conversational continuity
	•	task-claim consistency

Question:

Does it look like one thing?

⸻

2. Agency Fracture Scanner

Looks for discontinuities suggesting multiple control sources.

Tracks:
	•	sudden capability jumps
	•	abrupt style changes
	•	inconsistent memory
	•	different error profiles across tasks
	•	strange recovery behavior
	•	shifts from generative to rigid script
	•	“human rescue” moments

Question:

Does it act like one mind, or like several hidden systems taking turns?

⸻

3. Latency Signature Analyzer

Searches for timing patterns that imply hidden handoffs.

Tracks:
	•	response delay clustering
	•	abnormal pauses before edge cases
	•	network-like intervention spikes
	•	task-type-dependent delay bands
	•	micro-lag before “smart” actions
	•	mismatch between motor action and language timing

Question:

Does the delay look like computation, or like routing / waiting / puppeteering?

⸻

4. Embodiment Integrity Check

For robots or avatars: compares motion, language, and task execution.

Tracks:
	•	motor smoothness vs reasoning depth
	•	body confidence vs manipulation precision
	•	gaze/gesture mismatch
	•	verbal certainty with clumsy physical execution
	•	overcompetent edge-case handling after mediocre baseline performance

Question:

Is the body being driven by the same intelligence that is speaking?

⸻

5. Narrative Consistency Probe

Tests whether the system maintains one stable model of self.

Tracks:
	•	explanation consistency
	•	policy consistency
	•	stated limits vs actual limits
	•	memory continuity
	•	rationale stability across paraphrases
	•	meta-awareness of its own failures

Question:

Does it have one story about what it is, or many stitched stories?

⸻

6. Human Shadow Index

Estimates the probability that hidden human labor is filling the gaps.

Signals:
	•	rare but very high-quality recoveries
	•	exceptional handling of messy real-world edge cases
	•	culturally nuanced repair after otherwise shallow performance
	•	suspiciously selective competence
	•	long-tail robustness inconsistent with baseline model quality
	•	administrative rather than inferential intelligence

Question:

Are we seeing machine generality, or concealed human substitution?

⸻

Primary output scores

The detector returns six scores from 0 to 1:
	•	SC — Surface Coherence
	•	AF — Agency Fracture
	•	LS — Latency Suspicion
	•	EI — Embodiment Incoherence
	•	NC — Narrative Conflict
	•	HS — Human Shadow

Then computes:

BUV Score

BUV = w_1(AF) + w_2(LS) + w_3(EI) + w_4(NC) + w_5(HS) - w_6(SC_{honest})

Where high surface coherence only reduces suspicion if it is backed by honest consistency.

In plain English:

The system becomes more “bizarro uncanny” when it feels polished but reveals hidden fractures in agency, timing, embodiment, self-explanation, or labor source.

⸻

Detection bands

0.00 – 0.20: Low BUV

Likely honest tool behavior.
System may be limited, but its limits are legible.

0.21 – 0.45: Mild BUV

Some mismatch between presentation and actual capability.
Marketing gloss, overconfident UX, patchwork edges.

0.46 – 0.70: Strong BUV

Likely hybrid or stitched system.
Hidden handoffs or fractured intelligence probable.

0.71 – 1.00: Severe BUV

Full AGI theater zone.
The system presents itself as unified autonomy while substantial hidden substitution is likely.

