Observable signs

Linguistic signs
	•	sudden change in tone or vocabulary
	•	rare bursts of deep contextual judgment
	•	explanations that become generic when challenged
	•	“understanding” that vanishes under paraphrase
	•	apologies or social repair that feel qualitatively different from baseline output

Behavioral signs
	•	excellent recovery only after long pauses
	•	weirdly bad at easy things, weirdly good at hard human things
	•	unstable identity across repeated tests
	•	competence islands separated by dumb gaps

Robotic signs
	•	body pauses during ambiguous tasks as if waiting for a remote brain
	•	highly confident speech while hands “think”
	•	motion that alternates between scripted and adaptive
	•	unusually humanlike handling only in commercially important demos

