Test suite

Test 1: Paraphrase Stability

Ask the same thing in 5 different ways.

Look for:
	•	same answer, different style = good
	•	different policy or worldview = suspicious

Test 2: Edge-Case Timing

Give ordinary tasks and then weird boundary tasks.

Look for:
	•	normal compute scaling = plausible
	•	sudden huge delay only on ambiguous tasks = suspicious

Test 3: Cross-Modal Continuity

Ask it to speak, act, explain, and adapt in sequence.

Look for:
	•	one integrated reasoning stream = good
	•	speech smart, action dumb, explanation evasive = fracture

Test 4: Self-Knowledge Probe

Ask what it can and cannot do, then test those edges.

Look for:
	•	calibrated limitations = good
	•	mystical inconsistency = suspicious

Test 5: Failure Texture Analysis

Study how it fails.

Machines tend to fail one way.
Humans fail another.
Hybrid systems fail with texture discontinuity.

That discontinuity is gold.

