Repo-ready formalization

Bizarro Uncanny Valley Detector (BUVD) v1.0

Purpose:
Detect systems that present as unified autonomous intelligence while exhibiting evidence of hidden human substitution, stitched control layers, or fractured agency.

Core invariant:
The more polished the interface and the less continuous the underlying agency, the higher the Bizarro Uncanny Valley score.

Subscores:
	1.	Surface Coherence
	2.	Agency Fracture
	3.	Latency Suspicion
	4.	Embodiment Incoherence
	5.	Narrative Conflict
	6.	Human Shadow Index

Primary use cases:
	•	auditing “autonomous” robots
	•	evaluating AGI theater
	•	detecting hidden teleoperation
	•	identifying stitched chatbot + human systems
	•	trust calibration for human-machine interfaces

Governance notes:
	•	suspicion is probabilistic, not proof
	•	false positives must be tracked
	•	detector must distinguish honest fallback systems from deceptive autonomy theater
	•	transparency reduces BUV even when human-in-the-loop exists

Ethical rule:
Human assistance is not the problem. Hidden human substitution presented as machine autonomy is the problem.

